    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "We also ran into many issues; we changed many things along the way, maybe something might solve your issue: \r\n\r\n0. Take a look at [this repository for local deployment](https://github.com/provotum/poa-private-net) and this repository if you [plan to run it on the cloud](https://github.com/provotum/setup/tree/remote)\r\n1. Only add two sealers to `extradata` in your `genesis.json` (e.g. if you have 5 total nodes, only authorize 2 signers in extradata. (also check [EIP225](https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/issues/225))\r\n2. Add sleep between starting `miner.start()` on the two authorized nodes; somehow they raced and blocked each other when started too close together\r\n3. Add `--syncmode \"full\"` to your geth command",
